               <msContents>
                  <summary>Amyntas has learned that he will soon be ordered to go on a voyage, and he asks Zenon to have awnings and other things made for his boats and to bring them down with him when he returns to Alexandria.  He has sent Hermon to give a list of the things requirequired and to attend to the business of procuring them.</summary>
